Credit : © 1997 Paramount Pictures and Twentieth Century Fox / Courtesy Pyxurz .The movie " Titanic " , written and directed by James Cameron .Seen here , Kate Winslet as Rose DeWitt Bukater at the stern of the Titanic .Initial USA theatrical wide release December 19 , 1997 .Screen capture .© 1997 Paramount Pictures and Twentieth Century Fox .Credit : © 1997 Paramount Pictures and Twentieth Century Fox / Courtesy Pyxurz .Exploring the animal kingdom from the perspective of art , folklore and mythology .Menu .Sleeping Fox Screen Print .Throughout history the fox has been associated with the good and the bad .In pre - Christian Times the fox was seen as a symbol of the god of vegetation or as a symbol of forest and mountain - spirits .This later changed and the fox was seen as a demonic figure .The fox is very common in fables and is often seen as a trickster , he is depicted as greedy and dishonest .One of the best fables about a fox is the fox and the grapes .Interestingly it kind of sits between the two depictions of good fox / bad fox in that the foxes reaction to not being able to get the grapes is , well , very human !Aseops fable about the fox and the grapes introduces the expression " sour grapes " .The term later became an English idiom .It is an example of cognitive dissonance .One desires something , finds it unattainable , and reduces one 's dissonance by criticizing it .The original fable goes like this . "Driven by hunger , a fox tried to reach some grapes hanging high on the vine but was unable to , although he leaped with all his strength .As he went away , the fox remarked , ' Oh , you are n't even ripe yet !I do n't need any sour grapes ."
